# Docs and architecture

- Use ./docs as the primary context for how this project works. Start from ./docs/00-overview.md for stack, entrypoints, and data flow.
- Follow the layering and module boundaries in ./docs/01-architecture.md. This repo is frontend-only (HTML, SCSS/CSS, JS); no backend, DB, queues, or workers in-repo.
- Entrypoints are exactly landing.html, company.html, search.html. New pages must reuse the same header/footer structure and CSS link order (general → feature → paywall if needed). Do not introduce an SPA router.
- Do not invent new features, APIs, or persistence layers beyond what the user requests and what fits existing patterns described in ./docs.
